DA Leader Mmusi Maimane and DA Mayors to address the media on the country's unfolding social and economic crises. JOHANNESBURG - Democratic Alliance Leader, Mmusi Maimane, alongside DA Gauteng Mayors and will address the media on the country's unfolding social and economic crises. DA's address comes after violent protests broke out in Gauteng. In Johannesburg, over 90 people were arrested for looting shops and damaging property. READ: Xenophobia not behind Pretoria chaos: authorities Meanwhile, in Tshwane police are monitoring Marabastad after shacks were set alight on Monday afternoon. Maimane will be joined by senior leaders of the DA.